The paper deals with Bayesian mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves designing auctions and revenue maximization, which are topics in algorithmic game theory (cs.EC) and optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses duality theory, which is a mathematical tool commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
